# Line-ending policy. POSIX shell scripts and the `./taskkling` launcher MUST stay
# LF on every platform: a CRLF byte in a `#!/bin/sh` shebang breaks the interpreter,
# and `curl | sh` runs install.sh under /bin/sh regardless of the checkout's autocrlf.
*.sh        text eol=lf
/taskkling  text eol=lf

# Windows-only scripts keep CRLF.
*.cmd       text eol=crlf
*.ps1       text eol=crlf
